postcontent:
I have been experimenting with my carpentry skills lately and I am making gun cabinets with different American Flag designs that have hidden storage inside. You can find these online from various different websites for anywhere from $250-$450 not including shipping costs. I am making these here locally in the Tri-Cities in my spare time just as a hobby. The approximate measurements are 40 inches long, 26 inches high and 4 inches deep. This version of the flag will have 3 separate compartments. The lower half of the flag will open up to store shotguns or long guns. The top left and top right compartments will open up to store several handguns, magazines, holsters, ammo or whatever else you may want to put in it. I will include 4 gun magnets with screws that you can mount in any of the compartments in any configuration you want. The doors of the compartments are secured with magnetic child safety locks with magnet key. Just pass the magnet key over the outside of the door where the lock is located and it unlocks the door. There are no visible locks for anyone to see. The door hinges are European type cabinet hinges where nothing shows on the outside of the cabinet. So basically when you look at this, it just looks like a decorative flag that's hanging on your wall. I have several different paint schemes I can do. title: For Sale:  Original Nepalese P-1878 Francotte Short Lever Infantry Rifle
postcontent: Looks like shes soldOriginal Nepalese P-1878 Martini-Henry Francotte Pattern Short Lever Infantry Rifle, with bayonet With Original Bayonet, no missing parts, everything works, The action had very little rust, original working firing pin. The barrel has pitting on the underside. the bore looks to be in good shape shinny with some light fouling in the groves, good riffling.It came to me embedded in yak grease, I got as much off as possible without sanding or the use of harsh cleaners, I wanted to keep it as original as possible, no attempt was made to make this 139 year old relic look new, it is what it is a real old battlefeld war relic. it has factory stamps and markings on it.It had a small crack on the stock and minor wood chips or wood rot that have been repaired, some dents and chips ext that were left alone, this is a real battlefield rifle used by the Gurkha worriers.headspace has not been checked. I believe they used a black powder cartrige, it was not made to use the newer Martini henry smokeless powder loads. I'm not selling this as a shooter, it is a great collector display piece only. Hears the story: This Gurkha example was found in Military Storage in their homeland of Nepal, stored for over 100 years in not the best of circumstances.Nepalese 1878 Martini-Henry Francotte pattern short-lever rifle as created by Gen. Gahendra Rana’s cottage gun smiths in the 1880s. Put in storage no later than 1919 if not a decade or two sooner, this poor weapon was stored in an open-air 16th century castle with the only protection offered being yak grease until it was salvaged and brought over to the states a few years ago.This is a Nepalese P-1878 Francotte Pattern Short Lever Infantry Rifle.In 1878, the Francotte patent Martini System was granted utilizing a detachable mechanism fitted without the Cocking Indicator. Revolutionary at the time by compartmentalizing the mechanism for quick disassembly, it only lasted 10 years as the latest technology.stand not included, FFL not required.Will concider trades, Civil war WWI WWII Firearms or swords300.00
